rComments: Loved this class so much, i feel like it kept me stable during this whole semester!

Funny guy who actually cares about his students. His lectures aren't the best use of your time but the dgds are your best friend. Midterms and finals are very similar to past years (which he gives you).

Professor St Amant is hands down the best professor I have come across at the university. He is so caring, kind and respectful. He provides you with all the tools you need to succeed, including ALL the past exams which make for amazing studying material. He makes the class easy and helps you with anything you need. Overall, amazing prof.

One of the best profs i ever had, gave homework every week that wasnt worth too much so wed be forced to review the concepts, and we had infinite tries so if you didnt get it you could still learn. Great teaching and helped me a lot in later courses relearning the same concepts, memory was still fresh. Take him if you can he's great.

This prof is the best prof I've ever had. He explains things very well and is always in an upbeat, happy mood. His lecture notes are very well-made and with access to all the previous years exams, you have no reason to fail this class.

The best prof ever!! Gives you so many free points. It could be a hard class if your 12th grade chem knowledge is not strong, as he teaches really fast. Make sure to do many practice midterms and its an easy A!!

Hands down one of the most respected and inspirational prof at uottawa in sciences! He's awesome. Son cours est quand même très difficile, il faut se forcer pour bien comprendre en classe et faire tous les exercices/devoirs qu'il donne. Il donne accès aux anciens examens, ce qui facilite la réussite des élèves. 10/10
Hands down the best prof I've ever had. Quite a bit of work during the course, but if you do it all you are guaranteed to do well on exams. Provides great resources and help outside of class.
I really loved him! His exams were very straightforward, and you had an idea of what to expect.
Had fun in my chemistry class, most of the points are easy to get, the exams are a bit harder, but do the old exams and you should be fine. Would choose him again.

He gives you everything you need to do well. The way you are graded essentially gives you a free 40% through homework and labs. You can redo the homework as many times as you want and the labs are online simulations that are really quick and you can redo them. He's very clear about the contents of the exams and posts previous exams to study.

This was definitely a tough class, my grade 12 teacher wasn't great so I found that mr st-amant went through the material too fast. He posts all his old exams and takes the time to go through some of them in dgd's before exams. Overall really fun prof, but don't expect to understand if you're not paying attention or doing any work.

His labs and homework can be redone as many times as wanted. He posts all of his midterms and finals with the answers on his website since the year 2000, the formats don't change too much from one year to another. He tells you the type of 1-point questions that will be on tests. The final can replace midterms that weren't as successful.

As long as you actually put effort in, M. St-Amant gives you all of the resources you need to do well pass. He's an amazing prof who genuinely wants you to do well. The class itself is hard, but he will help you with extra DGDs and posting all old content/extra videos.

I feel like this prof gets a lot of hate but honestly try to teach a class with so much content and so much people attending it .Also people come rigth outside of high school expecting the same level of personalized care , thats just not going to happen in university specially in science or eng ( a ton of people).Overall solid choice.
teacherRatingTags: ['Tough grader', 'Beware of pop quizzes', 'Lots of homework']

rComments: A guaranteed30% of ur final grade through Labster&a.w.. Prof's great and provides his past exams so u know exactly what to expect. Wooclap's a way to stay focused during (a heavy)class for an extra10%. This class could NOT get any easier- The ppl complaining its difficult are the same 1s who couldnt play a game to earn the easiest20% of their lives

He does care for his students, but only those that do well. Those who dont get left behind in the dust. Hes hilarious and a genius, but honestly cant teach. He talks way too fast, zooms past material at light speed and honestly sounds like gibberish. Wooclaps the only reason I showed up to class. USE HIS WEBSITE TO THE FULLEST, do past exams.
Can't believe I pay 4000$ per semester and get a teacher like this. Doesn't teach - just read slides. I can read too buddy.

This prof is so bad. He literally doesn't teach - the class website is more useful than going to the lectures. He says average on exams is always 60% but that doesn't help him realize he's a bad teacher. Like wake up buddy obviously your students dont understand what ur teaching. Maybe it's time you try teaching instead of just reading your slides

Take the tutorials. He explain in details, taking his time and answering questions. Otherwise, it's a sprint. Many chances to get good grade, 30% on homework you can do as many times as you want, quiz in class that make you win but not loose points, term exams that you don't don't well at are saved for the final. Well organized. But do exercices!
He's a great teacher.
Great prof, really hard to fail this class

This prof was a blessing to have for my first term of university. If you did well in high school chemistry, you will have no problem. Attendance is important since there are interactive quizzes during lectures that are for marks. No labs, just online simulations which were honestly fun. Attend the DGDs before every exam and you will ace them.
Very good prof.

he has a bit of attitude sometimes, but always answers emails. He grades on so mnay things and there are SOOO many ways to get a good grade! He gives old midterms/exams which are EXACTLY like the ones you will get.

Best prof I had this semester, he gives you access to all the past midterms and exams which follow the exact same structure/format every time so you know exactly what to expect when you reach the exam. He's a STEM student's wet dream, take him if you get the chance!! He truly cares for students as well, always nice, but he doesn't take crap
He genuinely cares about his students and will take the time to help you if you go to office hours. Use the old exams he gives you!

I took an asynchronous class and I'm glad I chose this class. His exams are straightforward, provides lots of ways to practice, his grading is fair and tries to help out as much as possible. The course material was neatly organized into modules and it made it easy to comprehend concepts. Highly recommend this Prof!

My favourite prof so far. He very clearly wants his students to succeed, and gives lots of opportunities to do so. He posts all previous midterms and exams so you know exactly what to practice. His notes were well-explained and easy to follow. He made himself available to answer questions, and answered emails promptly. TAKE HIS COURSE.
midterm and final are very similar to the practice exam. Take advantage to the fact hes giving us acces to his old exam and answer key.

honestly this prof ain't it sis. his class is a joke. it's so easy because all you need to do to get an A+ is practice the previous exams that are posted on his website. his explanations aren't the best and he's boring (kinda rude too), but his class is so easy.

Amazing prof! Provides you with ALL the tools to succeed in this class as long as you put in the effort; Attend his classes, attend his DGD's or at least watch the recordings PRACTICE OLD EXAMS (key to your success). Always available to answer questions and his sense of humour makes the class a lot more fun! highly recommend.

He is the best prof I've had all semester. Both of our online labs and our online assignments had unlimited tries which is a free 30% added to your grade if you work for it. The professor himself is great and explains very well. Lots of work but easy A in the small assignments but his midterms are long so be prepared

The best teacher Ive had this semester. A real gem. He really wants you to succeed and he puts up all of his exam on his website. Labster and TA are really free point. I wished he was teaching another Chem class.

By far my favorite prof for my first term of uni. He offers a simple and easy transition from hs classes to university ones and sincerely cares about all of his students and their success. Always answers emails the same day. Doing the practice tests on his website is definitely the best preparation. If you succeeded in hs, you'll ace this class.

Amazing professor, he really does care about his students and has their best interest in mind. He's very understanding especially towards the whole online situation. His classes are organized and you will always know exactly what to expect on midterms and exams.
He's really nice. DO THE PRACTICE EXAM they are so helpful
Do the practice midterm on his website, they are really helpful.

Last year I had a bad teacher and honestly sucked at chem and because of that, I hated the class. But this year Prof St-Amant has actually made me like chemistry, he genuinely wants you to succeed and gives you soooo many resources to do so. If you do the work and do as many practice tests as possible before tests you will do fine. Great prof!

Very hard class but the prof is amazing. Super helpful, has countless resources available to students like video tutorials, website, practice exams... DO THE PRACTICE EXAMS they are soooo similar to the exams! Best advice I can give. Prof keeps class interesting with Kahoot sort of questions too lol. Teaches really well even though content is hard.
He's a really good prof, you just really have to work for it but you have all the resources on the site and he answer emails really quickly! Overall nice guy!
Fun teacher, explains very well and treats his students with a lot of respect.
he's aight

Awesome prof! His website has a bunch of old midterms so if you study from those you should be good. Definitely quite a lot of work with his weekly homework questions, 3 midterms and a cumulative final but it works in your favour
He's the best chimical teacher I've ever had!!!! if you have any problem just send him a message.
Not a good prof. His website is amazing but he is terrible. Its a shame he has to teach most chem classes. Good luck if youre stuck with him
This guy is serious about chem all while being the furthest thing from serious. Chill guy, hilarious, and motivational. Put the work in and you'll be fine.

The worst prof ever! I tried to set up a personal meeting with him several times, but he always refused. Frequently doesn't respond to emails. He forgot to post 2 last lectures online, and they were still tested on the final. He forgot to set up the online discussion group. I took the class in the summer, online. My CGPA was 9.1, now 8.5.

Vice-Dean/Prof. Alan-St Amant online chem course was pure self-effort where he has the same format for midterms/exam but changes up the numbers and marks very hard if you forget to do something in a question. Either get the question right for full marks or get very low (undeserving) part marks.
teacherRatingTags: ['Accessible outside class', 'Graded by few things', 'Tough grader']

rComments: St-Amant is a great professor. I love how he has so many options for the grade ponderation. Plus, his website is so well organized with exams from the past 19 years and so much more! Plus, he rounds up the grades up to 1 % if everyone does the teacher evaluation. He's also very accessible. However, I felt like I had to teach myself this class.
Best prof in the faculty of science. University is so lucky to have him. Hope they make him the dean of under graduate studies. What a gem, thank you

St Amand is a good prof. He always makes it known what's on the exam and exactly what he's grading. He has all the past year exams online so you have a good idea what to expect for his midterms. He has a good sense of humor and knows a lot about chemistry and if you ever have a question, he will reply to your email in no time! I recommend him.
He gives you all the ressources but his exams might seem the same but he tricks you... couldnt wait to be done with this class
tu peux avoir des points vraiment facilement ( echo360, labster, TA, ...)

Chem is not an easy A, but he gives you all the ressources you could need! His website has countless video tutorials, practice problems, all the notes in advance, he records all the lectures, etc, etc. Real funny guy and wants you to do well!
Honestly the best employee in faculty of science

HE'S LITERALLY THE BEST PROFE IN THE ENTIRE WORLD. HE GIVE THE SAME MIDTERMS AND FINALS EVERY YEAR. HE'S ALWAYS THERE WHEN YOU NEED HIM AND ANSWERS EMAIL QUICK QUICK. IF YOU TAKE THIS CLASS YOULL DEF PASS IT

He is an amazing chem prof. He gives lots of opportunities for you to do well. There are assignments (unlimited retries) which are worth 10%. All of his past exams are on his websites which are ALL you need to do for exam prep. Attendance isn't mandatory, but recommend so you can do echo360 worth 5%. 3 midterms and you can drop your worst one!!!

Amazing prof, the university should really adopt his website style: its extremely simple and everything is on one page. He records all his classes audio/video and he responds to emails extremely quickly. All previous year's tests are available on his website, they're the best way to study for this class.

Amazing Prof! He really cares about his students and gives good pointers! He gives all his time to insuring that students understand (DGD). Works on problems in class. Lots of opportunities to boost your average: online questions, weekly quizes, lab and 2 out of 3 midterms can count. Every time I've talked to him, he was inviting and so kind!

Professor St-Amant is a great professor when it comes to teaching a first year class. He tells you exactly what he expects for midterms and finals and even gives you past exams to practice with. Enjoyable class. Very passable even for those who dont necessarily like chemistry.

Honestly, great man. He is super passionate about chemistry which makes the class that is otherwise quite boring nice. Attendance is not necessary, he records his classes on echo 360 which are accessible online as well as some explanatory DGDs that are super helpful! He has a website "CHM 1711" which has absolutely everything you need for his class

Excellent professeur! Très drôle et répond en environ 2 heures à ses emails. La présence en classe n'est pas nécessaire, mais il y a des questions Echo360 qui comptent pour 10% de la note finale donc ça vaut la peine d'y aller! Tous ses examens et les corrigés depuis 2000 sont en ligne et son système de pondération avantage les élèves!

Le cours est tres facil. Ce qui va vous rendre fou ce sont ses examens IMPOSSIBLE a finir. Ils sont tres simple et il donne toutes les ressources pour les reussir, Mais vous n'aurez jamais une bonne note parce que vous n'aurez jamais le temps de repondre aux questions. Comprendre les methodes de resolution ne sert a rien, il faut les memoriser.

Actually the best prof for gen chem. He has a website, outside of virtual campus, that has everything you would ever need in this course - practice questions and podcast solutions, over 15 years of old exams and midterms, online discussion groups where HE actually explains the material and answers the questions. His assignments are really easy, too
Great prof, he's chill and gives you all the tools you need to succeed. DO PAST EXAMS.

Prof St-Amant is truly the greatest professor in the world, he's always super happy to talk to his students and is always ready to help you out. Whenever you need help, just email him and he usually answers in less than 2 hours. He gives you access to all his exams with the right answers up to the year 2000 so you can practice all you want. amazing
Excellent, pas besoin d'être un chimiste pour avoir un A+

J'ai adoré sa facon d'enseigner. Son francais rend parfois la comprehension de la matiere difficile. Les laboratoires aident à faire monter nos notes. On fait aussi 3 examens mais seulement 2 d'entre eux comptent (les meilleurs). La charge de travail est supérieure à celle des autres cours mais j'ai appris beaucoup. Le prof est drole/interessant.
Good prof, he likes lecture tool.

I guess he's a good teacher, but I don't like him as a person. He made me hate chem so much that I changed my programm. Everytime that someone says something stupid or give a bad answer he was like ''oh you must be in engeneering''. It's funny once, but not like every single class get over it. He puts all the previous tests online so it's easy.

Don't even bother looking over the lectures. Practice doing the midterms and exams on his website, he reuses the same questions every year. You will do really well if you just understand how to answer the questions.

I loved how he gave us A LOT of practice numbers and the exams and mid terms from the previous years.  Awesome resources on the course website to help understand.  Easy grades but you gotta work for them!

He does doesn't teach, he just reads his slides. Students that don't already know the concepts will have a hard time because he doesn't explain them. The labs are boring and the reports take a while to write but you can get a very high mark for the lab component, which boots your final grade. He answers emails really fast which is helpful.

Great prof, but his notes aren't clear enough though. Give the exams of the past 20 years and it's often the same questions, just make sure that you understand the concept clearly and not just the question as he often change the thing you need to find in the new exams.

Dr. St-Amant est un excellent prof de chimie. Il répond toujours à ces courriels et plein de ressources sont disponibles pour réussir. La clé pour réussir dans ce cours c'est de pratiquer plusieurs exercices. Les notes de cours vous mettent en contexte mais il faut SURTOUT faire des exercices. Les labs sont faciles si vous avez un bon partner
Merveilleux! Tellement de ressources, c'est assez facile à réussir

Best prof I've had in my whole life, seriously is it even possible to fail with this guy as your teacher ? So many resources, he even films his own classes so you can stay home and watch Breaking Bad (or not) .......... Anyways, I strongly recommend this guy for your chemistry class !
AMAZING. Lots of options. You cant fail this class
Very chill
Lots of past exams to practise with and they are basically the same as the next exam
Great prof but his notes doesn't make sense other that the online exams, do those and you can get a easy A. Would suggest the textbook only so you can get notes in class. Good luck

I loved this teacher, he knows his stuff really well and explains it well too. He gives you access to every exam from the last 15 years, with the corrected copies and podcasts explaining the tougher questions, so studying for exams is easy. He grades fairly, is very helpful and pretty funny too!

He is very helpful! You can have access to all the midterms and finals since 2000. Online DGD's are bless. Has online homework due weekly that are simple and explains mostly how they are done in the DGD's. He will answer your e-mail VERY QUICKLY. Whether it's 11:45pm Friday and the homework is due at 11:59pm or 2:37am Monday, he answers. LOVE him

Very helpful! He gives you all the midterms and finals since 2000 so there are no surprises. He also has online DGD's which can be useful. It's also easy to do well. You get up to 10 % for showing up and answering Lecture tool questions, 10 % for quick weekly online homework (with unlimited tries), labs are quite easy, etc.

He does a great job teaching such a big class (400 people) You need to go to class to answer the LectureTools questions (which is an easy 10%)  All of the past exams are online, and the exams are almost exactly the same, so if you do all past exams then you should do well. The hard part is the labs. Email the prof, he always answers & explains

ses explications en salle de classe ne sont pas toujours claires, mais il offre plusieurs ressources pour assurer la réussite de ses élèves/ plusieurs façons d'obtenir des points faciles dans le cours. il donne accès aux corrigés d'anciens examens pour se pratiquer. Il est essentiel de se presenter aux cours pour obtenir le 10% pour lecture tools.

J'ai eu beaucoup de mal à comprendre ses leçons. Le fait qu'on n'a pas de livre a rendu le travail encore plus difficile puisque ses notes de cours ne sont pas très claires. Et les exercices ne sont pas tous précisément corrigés. Je n'ai pas aimé sa méthode d'enseignement. Bref, j'ai vraiment galéré dans ce cours.
Il donne accès aux examens des années passés qui sont très représentatifs de l'examen. Répond vite au courriel. Pas de devoir excepté un travail assigné par semaine ( 3 questions ).

Mr St-Amant was honestly a great prof. I passed with a decent grade although I am not the strongest in chemistry. He is always willing to help and really cares about the students success. Great prof! I strongly recommend him! :)

Awesome Professor! His lectures are awesome. Everything you need to succeed is online and if you practice the past exams and midterms, you will end up with a really good mark. If I could, I would definitely take his class again. A+

I found this St-Amant gives really good lectures. However, some of the harder material which is harder to grasp was rushed, but we spent more time on easier concepts like Lewis structures than on the harder stuff. We didn't get to cover all the material towards the end of the semester, which is too bad since I will definitely take more chem classes

Un des meilleurs prof que j'ai jamais eu ! Super comique, interagit avec ses élèves , lecturetool c'est super le fun ! Une bonne manière d'apprendre tout en gagnant des points. Les exams sont raisonnable mais tu dois beaucoup travailler. Ses DGD en ligne sont super utile. répond toujours au courriel, bref ce prof est excellent !
Super easy to approach, his grading is fair and his exams are too. His explanations are kinda clumsy, but his online DGDs are very usefull!

Personnaly, I think the lectures are completely useless because you can't understand anything when he explains. His explanations (if you can even call it an explanation) are bad and incomplete. I feel like it's easy stuff that I've learned before but he makes it seems so hard.
Goes through lessons really fast without explaining it.
Nice teacher but awful notes Thinks you're the problem because he's been teaching the class for over 10 years

Ce prof est le prof le plus sweet que j'ai jamais eu, il fait toujours des jokes, et ris de ses propres jokes aussi! Il interagit avec les élèves des premières rangés et n'est pas vraiment sévère sur ses tests. Je reprendrais un cours avec ce prof n'importe quand!

Hilarious prof and easiest A in a science class you will probably ever have. If you were worried about 1st year chemistry, stop because you will be fine. Pros: lectures online (in video format!), tests online (all the way from 2000!), tests are always the same as past years, lots of examples (online dgds!). Cons: uhh no real dgds, I guess.

He let you know exactly what you had to do to get an A in his class. He gave three opportunities for writing a midterm and only 2 of them would count (best two obviously). He made podcasts so that you would look over the material, then in class he would go over them and do examples. All of his classes are online so you can review what you missed.

Overall the class is pretty easy. He gives the students access to all the tests from previous years which are basically identical to the ones he gives. He also does a lot of examples and always answers his emails. He's very helpful, however, his teaching is kind of confusing and as a visual learner I found that I had a lot of trouble following.

The teacher is good,but you need a personnal work .The bad thing is that it doesn't have a DGD, even if there was on-ligne it isn't like when you do it in a classroom.  and the use of lecturetools help .

He's one of those profs who lectures badly but gives great online resources. 14 yrs worth of corrected exams to practice from! He's a fair marker. His DGD's are online which is perfect if you don't live on campus, or just want to review what he said. Online homework is easy! NO TEXTBOOK :D  You won't regret taking a his class!

He's fun to listen to and keeps the lectures relaxed. however he has 3 tests before the finals and it's very difficult to predict your grade afterwards. let's just say not many people got good grades. the lectures are not mandatory but he does ask questions throughout that are worth 10% of the final grade. no in class dgd only online

Midterms and final exams dating all the way back to 2001 posted online with solutions for study purposes.  The way to pass this class with a good grade; don't miss lectures, do the online work, and do ALL of the past corresponding midterms. Excellent prof, the rest is just sitting back and listening to him pick on people, quite hilariously actually
My favorite prof in first year. He is funny and clear. He enjoys to chirp kids.
He chirps students with stupid questions, best part!
He keeps making jokes to make the class more interesting

Teacher has the ability to keep students interested and awake in his classes due to his humor and interactive pop quizzes via the website ''Lecture Tools''. However, I realized that most people who were understanding the lectures already knew the material before hand. If you don't know the material, better study online instead of attending classes.
Funny and chill teacher. Found he would go through the material really fast, but he was always happy to help you and answer questions if something was unclear.
Best teacher I have ever had, keeps chem interesting

To be honest, he is a nice guy but I hated him as a professor. Everything is online and you basically have to watch the podcasts and do everything yourself. It's extremely time-consuming and not something you want to do when you have 4 other hard classes. Going to lectures are almost pointless because he teaches you nothing. Just practice yourself.

One of the best profs I've ever had. Very down to earth, tries to make class stimulating with LectureTools (online multiple choice for extra points), really wants you to succeed, very approachable. His lectures are podcasts online which sometimes pile up and can be very dry but it's worth it having him as a prof.
Very funny

Awesome website! However, having to watch 1 h podcast before every lecture is very time consuming and boring. He uses his lecture time to go over examples and no theory. Challenging course since he changed the evaluation format this year compared to the past exams he did online. Do your homework and work hard on labs, that'll boost your average!

The teacher is great and very clear. He's very knowledgeable and I would recommend his class. The website is awesome to prepare yourself for quiz and exams. The material on the podcast is going to help you in the class. Great class and learned a lot, but be sure to study if you want good grades :)

In sum, a very experienced professor. Though there are no tutorials, I felt like class time was longer because you need to listen to podcasts prior to lectures. My advice, to succeed in his course is to practise for midterms with previous exams! He posts everything online which is very convenient! Very organized and has a sense of humour.

Listen to Podcasts, take notes, attend class, do the questions for each chapter and make sure you understand them, also do as many practice tests as you can and if something is not clear, theres a Facebook group where other students are willing to help. great class in general, very well organized!

He is really funny, makes the class laugh a lot. This year he decided to format of everything on us, and it did not benefit the class since he kept saying the average was lower. Midterms are alright, final is a lot harder. I don't think the podcasts are a good idea, classes were just pointless.

First of all, you learn everything online which is boring. All you do in class are lecture tools. He is not the best at explaining things, you must figure everything out practically on your own. Also he took away the DGD which help. For his midterms and exams, he tells you to practice the ones from the previous yearend you're all set. It's a LIE.

En général, je n'ai pas hais ce prof; il aime faire rire ses étudiants lors de ses cours et ça te garde réveillé. En tant que prof, il est correct mais je n'ai pas aimé devoir apprendre pratiquement tout la matière online au lieu qu'en classe! Honnêtement, j'aurais pu manquer la moitié des cours en classe et ça n'aurait rien changé...
He doesn't use a textbook, he is confusing, doesn't explain well and took away the discussion groups. I did not enjoy his class!
Il est un très bon prof et il explique bien la matière. j'adore son accent en francais, il est super drole. tres bon cours!
Great Teacher, Very helpful. His course is fairly hard, but he gives you a LOT of resources so you can practice a lot. I'm glad I had this teacher for my only chemistry course.

It was excellent that we didn't have to waste money on a textbook we wouldn't necessarily use. Also, he not only posted all the old exams (from 2000 onwards), but he made sure everyone knew exactly which questions were the same year to year.
Not too bad of a teacher. His TAs suck though.

His french is weird since he from Manitoba, might not understand some points hes trying to get across. Dont bother going to the DGDs since you can just listen to the podcasts online. Exams he posts are very helpful and almost identical to the ones he gives. A lot of material from this class is review from high school chemistry with few other things

Good Prof! Witty. Is really helpful and good in DGD's. Previous exams are posted online and are extremely helpful! Difficult class, so attending is very beneficial. If french is not your first language, he is a good prof to have, super easy to follow! No textbook needed which is great.

c'est le meilleur prof que j'ai Ce semestre!!!!!!il m'a repondu a tous questions que j'ai pose (meme les questions qui n'ont aucune relation avec le calcul qu'on aura a l'examen c-a-d de comprehension), les examens sont extremement facile et sont tres similaires aux annes precedentes et VERY NICE AND FUNNY GUY!!
BEAUCOUP D'ÉNERGIE, DEVOIRS TRÈS UTILES -> MÊME CHOSE QU'EXAMEN
Not a bad teacher!!

No text book, previous exams are on the web and helps a lot! DGD's are the only place where you actually do actual numbers that are on the exam since in class its a lot of theory... You'll probably wanna fall sleep especially on those 8:30 classes

A very organized prof that replies to emails almost instantaneously. The 'uuh, OK, shhh' could be toned down though. Midterms and exams are really close to previous years' exams (maybe a little harder), but you should be okay if you practice and do all the homework! No single reference to the textbook which was PERFECT! Overall, recommended. :)

He was a good prof and he was really funny, maybe for him to improve is to change the course outline for those who hasn't done the highest chemistry in college (CEGEP) or in high school. Even though I end up getting more help at the end. I would said don't take his class if you knew to get the minimum of 65% for the nursing program for Ottawa U.

Excellent and very organized prof. All the notes are online, and crystal clear. He tends to speak a little fast sometimes, but just read the notes and you'll be fine. He gives you all the past midterms and finals, so just practice those and you should do great. He's also very funny during the lectures.
Good Teacher although, the class is difficult. Attending class is important in order to understand what the teacher wants!

I did not like this prof, he was the last one to show up to class and always the first to leave.  He always talked really fast and he did not explain things very clearly. If you review the past exams you should do ok on the mid-terms and final, good luck.

Good professor, however the only high point of his class is when he makes a little joke or tells a funny story, other than that, you're struggling to stay awake (especially at 8:30 a.m). Review the past exams and you will do good.

En général, un professeur plutôt drôle et sympathique, mais n'oublié pas qu'il est un professeur avant tout. Gars à ceux qui l'ont en français!
